03:13:27.320 --> 03:13:32.360
[Amit Varma]: to cover incident of communal violence after violence after violence eventually you know

03:13:32.360 --> 03:13:39.400
[Amit Varma]: it could bleed into one but what you have done in your writing and in fact you know just your

03:13:39.400 --> 03:13:46.040
[Amit Varma]: description of one of the deaths at cheetah camp is an example of that is that you took that deeper

03:13:46.040 --> 03:13:51.720
[Amit Varma]: look and humanize a person like you could easily say that uh you know a muslim boy was in a room

03:13:51.720 --> 03:13:57.400
[Amit Varma]: and the police burst in and they took him out and they killed him but instead we know that he's a

03:13:57.400 --> 03:14:02.200
[Amit Varma]: zari worker his name is abdullah he's writing a letter to a friend in kuwait about the birth of

03:14:02.200 --> 03:14:07.880
[Amit Varma]: his child and then the police burst in and take him out and this just humanizes the whole thing

03:14:07.880 --> 03:14:12.680
[Amit Varma]: immediately there is empathy and it's in fact really cinematic like if you had a web series

03:14:12.680 --> 03:14:18.360
[Amit Varma]: on communal violence your opening scene could just be the letter being read out and whatever

03:14:18.360 --> 03:14:22.040
[Amit Varma]: and then that sudden burst and the shock of the police and the violence and all of that

03:14:23.160 --> 03:14:30.440
[Amit Varma]: this gaze did you work at developing it was it partly um a sort of a strategic thing that for

03:14:30.440 --> 03:14:35.320
[Amit Varma]: my stories to be powerful this is what i have to do is it something that was taught to you

03:14:35.320 --> 03:14:40.200
[Amit Varma]: or that you learned over time by yourself or was it always just natural to you tell me a little

03:14:40.200 --> 03:14:45.080
[Amit Varma]: bit about the craft of doing this kind of reporting to make it affect i don't think anything is just

03:14:45.080 --> 03:14:52.040
[Guest]: entirely natural or is entirely taught right it's both correct so but if you're serious about what

03:14:52.040 --> 03:14:57.800
[Guest]: you're doing and i think i was extremely serious and honest about reporting on communal violence

03:14:57.800 --> 03:15:03.480
[Guest]: very honest i was always interrogating myself how do i put it down how do i communicate this

03:15:03.480 --> 03:15:08.200
[Guest]: because you know you are writing on something which is potentially uh you're going to reach

03:15:08.200 --> 03:15:13.240
[Guest]: people you enjoy a certain credibility then you it's all the more reason why you should be doing

03:15:13.240 --> 03:15:20.280
[Guest]: it extremely carefully before i try and answer it further i want to give you one more example

03:15:21.400 --> 03:15:28.840
[Guest]: of something like this in 1991 i was covering the rath yatra that rath yatra and uh that takes

03:15:28.840 --> 03:15:35.400
[Guest]: place in jamalpur every year ahemdabad i was in business india and i was lucky in business india

03:15:35.960 --> 03:15:40.280
[Guest]: allowed that space to explore the issue a little bit so it was not just like newspaper coverage

03:15:40.280 --> 03:15:47.400
[Guest]: where you were covering on a day-to-day basis so it was a particularly uh uh brutal brutalizing

03:15:47.400 --> 03:15:54.280
[Guest]: period that was happening all along because uh uh you had seen that whole development post 1986

03:15:54.280 --> 03:16:01.800
[Guest]: and then of course it culminated in 2002 like i've written about but 1991 i actually traveled

03:16:01.800 --> 03:16:07.560
[Guest]: by train from bombay to baroda surat then surat to baroda surat then finally ended up in himmat

03:16:07.560 --> 03:16:12.520
[Guest]: nagar ahemdabad and i kept talking to people including businessmen who happened to be hindu

03:16:12.520 --> 03:16:19.320
[Guest]: and one just was really appalled by the level of crass hate that was being openly spoken about

03:16:19.320 --> 03:16:24.680
[Guest]: about the muslim minority but that apart that also reflected in my business story but

03:16:25.560 --> 03:16:31.000
[Guest]: uh this particular incident i remember being really very very horrified by which is that

03:16:32.360 --> 03:16:39.160
